Two things can be said with certainty about websites in 2016:

1.Websites are not what they used to be.

 

2. The internet is not what it used to be.

It used to be that a person who had 10k to drop on a site, would do so with the hope that maybe their site would strike gold. It used to be that there wasn't a way for people to learn about your site outside of an email or someone verbally telling them about it. Now people can find a company on any social media platform, on Google, or Yelp, or Amazon. In a lot of ways this isn't different from how people clicking on links in an email that was forwarded to them. They clicked on the link because they trusted the person who sent it to them. At Ghettifish Inc. our objective for you and your website is simple: Find the platform that your audience is active on and build a camp for your brand there. We do that through analyzing your industry and building a profile for your core audience that we can use to design relevant media for that audience to consume. This used to be as easy as getting in touch with your "Web guy" and having them throw something together for you.     [/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row admin_label="Row"][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section admin_label="Section" fullwidth="on" specialty="off"][et_pb_fullwidth_image admin_label="Fullwidth Image" src="https://ghettifish.com/app/uploads/2016/02/low-looking-slide-2-02.png" show_in_lightbox="off" url_new_window="off" use_overlay="off" animation="left" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"] [/et_pb_fullwidth_image][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section admin_label="Section" fullwidth="off" specialty="off" transparent_background="off" background_color="#000000" allow_player_pause="off" inner_shadow="off" parallax="off" parallax_method="off" padding_mobile="off" make_fullwidth="off" use_custom_width="off" width_unit="on" make_equal="off" use_custom_gutter="off"][et_pb_row admin_label="Row"][et_pb_column type="1_2"][et_pb_text admin_label="Text" background_layout="dark" text_orientation="left" use_border_color="off" border_color="#ffffff" border_style="solid"]

People are waiting for you to show them what you've got.

We come up with a hypothesis about where those people are on the web and what it takes to earn their trust.

Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my website. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: What is Ghettifish?
item.dc:creator: nicbovee
item.content:encoded: Ghettifish is our mascot and symbolizes the creative thinking (spaghetti on the wall) and jellyfish-like efficiency we bring to every project. Whether you are a small business owner or Fortune 500 company, we are in business to help you connect and interact with the right people online. Your passion is our difference Your passion is our difference We channel every last drop of your company's passion into everything we do online. The "Why" behind what you do let's people trust you, understand you, and relate to you. We want people to like you, and for that to happen they need to trust you. The problem with Digital Agencies in 2017 Ghettifish was created to solve a problem that seemed to be happening everywhere we turned. Websites are built far too often as quickly as possible with no consideration of the company brand identity, or the goals in mind. Why do you NEED a website? Why do you NEED that logo? What is it all for? Intentionality is at the core of everything we do. The average agency is going to find out your mission statement and flop your company into whatever the best-rated Wordpress template is available at the time. This approach is certainly a quick and dirty way to mark something off of a checklist but doesn't really have your business or your customer in mind. We are shifting that mentality by thoroughly understanding your customer's needs and your company's needs before we even start a project. We've built and refined a process that is geared for accomplishing our mission.

What is there to learn about HTML5?

Coding and website designing is actually extremely complicated, once you've looked into the history of it.

Since reading about HTML5, I now have a basic understanding of the two reasons why it exists:

1.) To be compatible with all older types of markup.

HTML5 is an attempt to unite all forms of markup from before, so that nobody has to scrap everything that they've learned in their past experience of coding.

2.) To provide a fresh platform where additions and updates are encouraged.

In addition to flowing with all other attempts at a universal markup language, HTML5 acts as a building point for more versions and ideas to be added on- without redesigning the whole system.

 

The idea behind HTML5 is to be the compromise between the old and the new that is coming, to simplify and correct all of the problems with older versions and attempts at doing the same.

This tutorial will show you how to add Photo Buttons that you can move around anywhere you would like them.

 

1. Start on any page you would like to add them to and Click Add Row.

2. Click Add From Library.

3. Click Photo Buttons.

4. Click on the hamburger icon to access the settings for the Photo Button.

5. Open your Wordpress Dashboard on a sperate tab and hover over Media and click library.

6. Select the image you would like to use.

7. In the image info window, click on the URL field and use the select all keyboard shortcut and then use the copy shortcut.

8. Go back to the tab your photo button is open on and paste between the URL between the quotes after src=".

9. Paste the link to the page your button will direct to after href=" between the quotes.

10. Add the button text between the <h1> Tags.

11. Save the module, and update the page.

12. Your Photo Button module is ready to go, and can be moved into place anywhere on the page.

item.title: Semantics: A search for meaning.
item.dc:creator: nicbovee
item.content:encoded:
According to the dictionary, Semantics is the branch of linguistics and logic concerned with meaning.

In order for us to design, we must first search for the meaning within what it is we are designing. We must search for information on the product, company, competition, its destination, the end user, or the real meaning of the subject or its roots. If we want to design well, we must aim our efforts at a greater understanding of accurate definitions behind the subject. Semantics are the bedrock for the project and a necessity for the design.

According to the designers, Semantics means understanding the subject in all aspects; to create a connection by speaking both the language of the sender and receiver.

Each detail is a tiny decision and the more we focus on semantics the more decisions we can make as a designer and the more the end user will find "God in the details".
